04:48.102 --> 04:49.768
23rd floor.

04:51.572 --> 04:55.841
George Caplan? I'm Anastasia.

05:00.114 --> 05:01.646
Thank you for meeting me here.

05:01.682 --> 05:03.215
I'm intrigued.

05:03.251 --> 05:06.018
You must be quite a
powerful man to merit this.

05:06.053 --> 05:08.520
That's why I need you
to keep it between us.

05:08.555 --> 05:10.489
- Can you do that?
- Of course.

05:10.524 --> 05:12.457
That's what we do.

05:12.493 --> 05:15.761
As long as this stays in
place, I'm yours completely.

05:17.765 --> 05:20.399
The three of us then?

05:20.637 --> 05:23.402
Just... just me.

05:23.408 --> 05:25.304
Please have a seat.

05:27.375 --> 05:28.941
Last words of advice.

05:28.976 --> 05:31.443
Do what you have to do
to get what you need.

05:31.478 --> 05:34.013
She's just a piece of company property.

05:39.720 --> 05:41.653
Anastasia was it?

05:41.688 --> 05:45.190
- It's really nice to meet you.
- Likewise.

05:47.194 --> 05:49.361
It's real. Go ahead.

05:49.397 --> 05:51.063
Music.

05:56.904 --> 06:00.339
So let me explain.
That... that man is my father,

06:00.374 --> 06:02.174
and I have a... a problem.

06:02.209 --> 06:05.044
It's not physical.

06:05.079 --> 06:07.980
Dad thought that this might help.

06:08.015 --> 06:09.815
I understand.

06:11.718 --> 06:14.519
Just relax, and let me do everything.

06:32.683 --> 06:33.372
Oh, jeez, sorry.

06:33.407 --> 06:35.080
I didn't think you'd get here so fast.

06:35.081 --> 06:36.342
Can I have a few minutes?

06:36.377 --> 06:38.243
- Oh, of course.
- Thank you.

06:44.507 --> 06:47.519
Can you tell me about yourself first?

06:47.554 --> 06:51.190
It's a... it's a trust thing.

06:51.225 --> 06:53.325
What do you wanna know?

06:53.763 --> 06:55.560
Where are you from?

06:55.596 --> 06:58.730
What are your passions?

06:58.765 --> 07:00.532
Let's see...

07:00.567 --> 07:04.203
My parents were diplomats, so
I grew up all over the world.

07:04.238 --> 07:07.006
Attended a girls' school in Switzerland.

07:07.041 --> 07:09.041
The campus was way out in the country...

07:09.076 --> 07:11.543
no boys around for miles.

07:11.578 --> 07:13.112
Sometimes, when we got lonely,

07:13.147 --> 07:14.613
my roommate, Silvie, and I used to...

07:14.648 --> 07:18.717
Okay, look, I know
this is a little weird,

07:18.752 --> 07:22.821
but if this is gonna work,
I need the real you.

07:22.856 --> 07:26.791
Not that softcore bullshit
they make you memorize.

07:26.827 --> 07:29.361
Please?

07:29.397 --> 07:31.263
If it helps, I guarantee

07:31.298 --> 07:33.765
that I will not keep you very long.

07:41.509 --> 07:43.642
Come on. Where... where
are you really from?

07:43.677 --> 07:46.645
Mr. Caplan, you know
I can't tell you that.

07:47.526 --> 07:49.714
Okay. Mr. Caplan.

07:49.750 --> 07:51.450
Message received.

07:52.920 --> 07:54.719
It must be exhausting.

07:54.755 --> 07:58.290
Losers like me blather on
all day about our problems.

08:00.127 --> 08:01.660
Well...

08:01.695 --> 08:05.931
I can tell you my parents
weren't diplomats.

08:05.966 --> 08:07.766
Oh, yeah?

08:07.801 --> 08:11.236
What did your dad really do?

08:11.272 --> 08:12.837
Nothing interesting.

08:12.873 --> 08:14.673
My dad negotiates grain contracts.

08:14.708 --> 08:16.475
It has to be more interesting than that.

08:28.667 --> 08:30.021
My father...

08:30.057 --> 08:33.924
he had a little restaurant
in Franklin Heights.

08:33.961 --> 08:36.260
Had?

08:36.297 --> 08:38.897
It's gone now.

08:38.932 --> 08:41.633
I'm sorry.

08:41.668 --> 08:43.434
I just made you sad, didn't I?

08:46.673 --> 08:48.107
I'm not sad.

08:48.142 --> 08:50.842
I'm very happy to be here with you.

08:50.877 --> 08:52.544
Separate building systems.

08:52.580 --> 08:54.513
Ben was right about you.

08:54.548 --> 08:57.983
- Ben...
- Ben Larson.

08:58.018 --> 09:00.185
He's a... he's a friend from work.

09:00.221 --> 09:01.987
He said you were special.

09:02.022 --> 09:04.889
Ben Larson?

09:04.925 --> 09:06.658
Never heard of him.

09:06.693 --> 09:08.627
It's okay.

09:08.662 --> 09:10.862
We're alone.

09:10.897 --> 09:13.298
How did you two meet?

09:13.334 --> 09:15.800
What does this about?

09:15.836 --> 09:19.371
It's about Ben Larson.

09:19.406 --> 09:22.174
I told you. I don't know him.

09:22.209 --> 09:25.144
Well, I think you do.

09:25.179 --> 09:29.781
And you're gonna tell
me the truth right now.

09:29.816 --> 09:31.351
The truth?

09:31.352 --> 09:32.717
AIR PURIFICATION SYSTEM:
ACCESS RESTRICTED

09:32.753 --> 09:34.353
Sure. The truth is that with your pants off,

09:34.388 --> 09:38.190
all you limp dicks look the same to me.

09:38.225 --> 09:39.591
No...

09:41.395 --> 09:44.496
Now I am going to ask you again,

09:44.532 --> 09:46.465
and if you don't answer...

09:46.500 --> 09:48.733
then I start carving.

09:48.769 --> 09:53.038
Maybe they fix ya; maybe
they just let ya scar up.

09:53.073 --> 09:55.974
Do you know where Spiga
sends girls like that?

09:56.009 --> 09:59.344
To the silos to service the grain crews.

09:59.380 --> 10:01.513
You can cut me.

10:01.549 --> 10:03.948
I've been cut many times before.

10:03.984 --> 10:06.385
A client used to hold
my head under water...

10:06.420 --> 10:10.021
said it helped him cope with
the stress from the office.

10:10.057 --> 10:12.023
There is nothing you can dream up

10:12.059 --> 10:14.259
in your sick, twisted imagination

10:14.295 --> 10:16.127
that I have not endured in this job.

10:16.163 --> 10:20.399
- Come on.
- So go ahead. Make me scream.

10:20.434 --> 10:22.301
But you'll get the same answer.

10:23.604 --> 10:26.171
I don't know Ben Larson.

10:27.541 --> 10:29.808
How deep do you want me to go?

10:29.843 --> 10:33.612
However deep you want.

10:37.041 --> 10:38.578
