11:37.320 --> 11:39.687
Ben, the presentation
is in ten minutes.

11:39.723 --> 11:41.622
Where are you?

11:41.658 --> 11:44.024
The presentation. Right. I...

11:44.060 --> 11:46.193
Sorry, I'm... I had to
take care of something.

11:46.229 --> 11:48.363
I'm on my way.

11:50.866 --> 11:54.193
ROGER CAPLAN:
SUBJECT ENTERING TO RED ZONE

12:36.345 --> 12:38.112
- Come on, let's go again.
- Laura...

12:38.147 --> 12:39.747
No, I know. I get it.

12:39.783 --> 12:42.750
I dropped my guard. I tensed up.
Let's just go again.

12:42.786 --> 12:44.952
The point of Past Trauma
Re-experiential Therapy

12:44.987 --> 12:46.854
is not to pound your
trauma into submission.

12:46.890 --> 12:48.289
It's to explore every facet

12:48.324 --> 12:50.491
of what's causing your emotional pain.

12:50.527 --> 12:52.993
Fine. Let's explore it.

12:53.029 --> 12:54.995
Go again.

12:55.031 --> 12:56.431
We need to talk about your feelings.

12:56.466 --> 12:58.332
Oh, my God.

12:58.367 --> 13:00.635
That's how this works? You
want it to work, don't ya?

13:00.670 --> 13:03.471
Look, I have tried cognitive
enhancement diversion,

13:03.506 --> 13:07.041
wearables, drugs, even a goddamn VR pet,

13:07.076 --> 13:08.676
and now this crap.

13:08.711 --> 13:11.078
It's all bullshit.

13:11.113 --> 13:12.747
Everyone things that they
know what I went through,

13:12.782 --> 13:14.315
but they don't.

13:20.089 --> 13:21.489
I have to go.

13:29.532 --> 13:32.166
- Where the hell were you?
- I got held up.

13:32.201 --> 13:33.768
The Deck isn't even finished yet.

13:33.803 --> 13:36.103
It's fine.

13:36.138 --> 13:38.339
I got this.

13:41.344 --> 13:44.044
- Mr. Larson, you're late.
- I know.

13:44.080 --> 13:46.246
- I told you...
- I'm sorry.

13:46.816 --> 13:48.851
ROGER CAPLAN:
ARRIVING AT FRANKLIN HEIGHTS JUKU

13:48.852 --> 13:50.651
Ben...

13:50.941 --> 13:53.521
Go.

14:00.930 --> 14:03.598
Counterintelligence used to...

14:03.633 --> 14:05.633
Sorry.

14:08.671 --> 14:10.237
Counterintelligence used to be about

14:10.272 --> 14:13.007
breaking into security
systems and databases,

14:13.042 --> 14:14.709
but now, thanks to Everclear,

14:14.744 --> 14:17.812
it's about breaking into the human mind.

14:17.847 --> 14:20.381
We no longer rely on outdated
interrogation techniques.

14:20.416 --> 14:23.250
We can now literally
turn people's brainwaves

14:23.285 --> 14:27.822
into usable images and
actionable intelligence.

14:32.228 --> 14:34.128
Boris...

14:34.163 --> 14:36.931
what the hell is wrong with you?

14:36.966 --> 14:39.033
Lack of good role models probably.

14:43.640 --> 14:46.206
Are you sure this is the place?

14:46.242 --> 14:49.076
Girl's a high-end spreader
from Franklin Heights.

14:49.111 --> 14:51.012
This is where they got her.

14:51.047 --> 14:53.948
Of course, if you want some
A-plus brainiac yum-yum...

14:53.983 --> 14:57.451
You're disgusting and
I hate that I know you.

14:57.486 --> 14:59.186
Nice doing business.

14:59.221 --> 15:02.190
We're reopening a background
check into one of your students.

15:02.191 --> 15:05.325
She was recruited into
Arcadia a few years ago?

15:06.160 --> 15:08.195
Elena Marquez.

15:08.230 --> 15:10.130
That takes me back.

15:10.166 --> 15:13.467
We didn't have an empty
seat in those days.

15:13.502 --> 15:15.069
You have one or two kids stroke out,

15:15.104 --> 15:17.504
and you're a pariah.

15:17.540 --> 15:20.675
- Is Elena in trouble?
- No... no, nothing like that.

15:20.710 --> 15:22.176
A high-level Spiga executive

15:22.211 --> 15:23.678
is interested in acquiring her contract,

15:23.713 --> 15:25.446
but we're having trouble
reaching her next of kin

15:25.481 --> 15:27.281
to update the payout agreements.

15:27.316 --> 15:29.684
Those sealed Arcadia
personnel files are

15:29.719 --> 15:31.385
a real pain in the ass.

15:31.400 --> 15:32.416
STUDENT DATABASE

15:34.057 --> 15:38.993
Technically, my files should
be locked just as tight.

15:46.502 --> 15:48.435
There's only one contact for her.

15:48.471 --> 15:51.639
- How do you want it?
- Quietly.

15:51.674 --> 15:53.975
By isolating the neurons
in sectors one-four-seven,

15:54.010 --> 15:56.176
in one-four-nine, and one-six-two,

15:56.212 --> 15:57.612
my team has had remarkable success

15:57.647 --> 15:59.446
in extracting actionable data.

15:59.482 --> 16:01.115
And best of all, we can remove the data

16:01.150 --> 16:03.684
with precision at the end
of the employee's contract

16:03.720 --> 16:06.787
without causing permanent
damage as we have in the past.

16:06.823 --> 16:08.322
Why erase everything when we can erase

16:08.357 --> 16:10.524
only our proprietary information?

16:14.530 --> 16:17.431
We hope to have Everclear online
within the next three months.

16:17.466 --> 16:21.368
Unless you have any
questions, that's all I have.

16:21.403 --> 16:23.738
Let me ask just one question.

16:23.773 --> 16:26.874
We're a bio-tech company, correct?

16:26.909 --> 16:28.575
- Yes.
- And our firm focuses on

16:28.611 --> 16:30.277
the development of genetic strains,

16:30.312 --> 16:32.680
new agricultural products,
and the production of food

16:32.715 --> 16:35.716
- for the entire goddamn world?
- Yes.

16:35.752 --> 16:37.718
Then if you could explain
to me what the hell

16:37.754 --> 16:39.854
we need a mind-reading device for.

16:39.889 --> 16:41.956
It's okay. I'll handle this.

16:41.991 --> 16:45.726
Expenditures for prevention
of intellectual theft

16:45.762 --> 16:49.697
account or a full 40%
of our security budget.

16:49.732 --> 16:54.268
Everclear allows us to apply
those funds elsewhere.

16:54.303 --> 16:56.737
And what about the millions
you've already spent?

16:56.773 --> 16:58.539
It will shore up the security gaps

16:58.574 --> 17:00.675
I've already flagged for you.

17:01.465 --> 17:02.910
The gaps that almost allowed

17:02.945 --> 17:05.945
Chad Peterson to steal our protocols.

17:05.982 --> 17:08.315
To the next of kin of Elena Marquez,

17:08.349 --> 17:10.550
we regret to inform you that
your daughter's contract

17:10.586 --> 17:12.519
has been terminated prematurely.

17:12.555 --> 17:15.189
If you would like to receive
the full death benefit payout,

17:15.223 --> 17:18.492
please meet our representative
at the address on record tonight

17:18.527 --> 17:22.462
at... 5:30 p.m.

17:22.498 --> 17:24.131
Letterhead and send.

17:27.435 --> 17:29.770
David, I know we haven't
always seen eye to eye,

17:29.806 --> 17:32.306
but if you are questioning
my performance...

17:32.341 --> 17:34.709
What I am questioning are
the time and resources

17:34.744 --> 17:36.844
you're continuing to spend
on a white rhino chase.

17:36.879 --> 17:40.614
Everclear is not a white rhino, sir.

17:40.649 --> 17:43.417
It's going to be operational
within the month actually.

17:43.452 --> 17:45.019
Oh, really?

17:45.054 --> 17:48.589
Then why does your
presentation not reflect that?

17:48.624 --> 17:52.793
Because Ms. Krauss taught
me to never over-promise.

17:52.829 --> 17:57.064
But it will be up and
running by month's end.

17:57.100 --> 17:59.700
Thank you, Mr. Larson.

17:59.736 --> 18:01.401
We'll reconvene and hear

18:01.437 --> 18:04.939
the next candidate's
presentation in one hour.

18:08.978 --> 18:11.411
Ben...

18:14.217 --> 18:18.018
I'm sorry. I overstepped my bounds.

18:18.054 --> 18:21.021
I appreciate your loyalty.

18:21.057 --> 18:22.589
Of course.

18:22.625 --> 18:25.659
Just be careful.

18:25.694 --> 18:28.462
You made some big claims in there.

18:28.497 --> 18:30.530
We all need to make sure we deliver.

18:30.566 --> 18:33.033
Yes, ma'am.

18:40.410 --> 18:44.174
6 YEARS AGO

18:44.274 --> 18:46.446
Please be advised.

